line_1: I heard: and lo! at once controul'd,
Or senates stand by patriot mobs controul'd?
line_2: Or shall each schismatic your faith new mould,

line_1: Thus each by turns the realm controul'd,
line_2: Which each in turn despair'd to hold;

line_1: Has broke thro' greater, stronger Powers controul'd,
line_2: Two mighty Obstacles; tho' Love of Old

line_1: Had doom'd themselves; whence oft, when Night controul'd
line_2: The funeral Dirge, they down the Torrent rowl'd:

line_1: Had doom'd themselves; whence oft, when Night controul'd
line_2: The World, returning hither their sad Spirits howl'd.

line_1: The man by no mean fears or hopes controul'd,
line_2: Who serves thee from affection, not for gold!

line_1: How wild Desires should be controll'd;
line_2: And how much brighter Virtue was, than Gold;

line_1: Scorning to be by God, or Man control'd;
line_2: While Hophni and Phinehas both in Sin grow bold,
